    {
      "id": "r001",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "Claude Code supports 18 hook events including PreToolUse and PermissionRequest. Both fire before tool execution and can return allow/deny decisions via JSON. HTTP hooks (type: 'http') POST event data to a URL and accept synchronous JSON responses — this is the native integration point for a remote dashboard.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code hooks reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "hooks",
        "http",
        "PreToolUse",
        "PermissionRequest"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r002",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "PermissionRequest hooks receive permission_suggestions (the 'always allow' options users see) and can respond with decision.behavior='allow'|'deny' plus updatedPermissions. PreToolUse hooks can return permissionDecision='allow'|'deny'|'ask'. Both support updatedInput to modify tool arguments before execution.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code hooks reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "hooks",
        "permissions",
        "API-surface"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r003",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "Hook input (POST body) includes: session_id, transcript_path, cwd, permission_mode, tool_name, tool_input, tool_use_id, agent_id, agent_type. This gives a remote dashboard full context about what Claude is doing and why.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code hooks reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "hooks",
        "context",
        "session-data"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r004",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "HTTP hook timeout defaults to 30 seconds (configurable up to 600s). Non-2xx responses or timeouts are non-blocking errors — execution continues. This means if the dashboard server is down, Claude Code doesn't hang, but permissions fall through to the local terminal.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code hooks reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "hooks",
        "timeout",
        "fault-tolerance"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r005",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "Hook configuration lives in settings files: ~/.claude/settings.json (user-wide), .claude/settings.json (project), .claude/settings.local.json (personal, gitignored). HTTP hooks support header interpolation with allowedEnvVars for auth tokens.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code settings reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "hooks",
        "configuration",
        "auth"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r006",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "PostToolUse and PostToolUseFailure hooks fire after execution and are non-blocking. These can feed the live activity stream — every tool call, success or failure, gets reported to the dashboard without affecting Claude Code's performance.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code hooks reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "hooks",
        "activity-feed",
        "PostToolUse"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r007",
      "type": "risk",
      "topic": "integration",
      "content": "Hook JSON config is loaded at session startup. Mid-session changes require /hooks menu interaction or session restart. This means the dashboard can't dynamically reconfigure which tools need approval without restarting Claude Code.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code hooks reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
