    },
    {
      "id": "r011",
      "type": "recommendation",
      "topic": "architecture",
      "content": "Recommended architecture: Node.js HTTP server on localhost receives hook POSTs from Claude Code. Server holds pending permission requests in memory. Browser connects via WebSocket for real-time push. User approves/denies in browser, server responds to the held HTTP request. PostToolUse hooks feed activity stream. claims.json watched via fs.watch for sprint dashboard updates.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "analysis",
        "artifact": null,
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "web",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "architecture",
        "WebSocket",
        "Node.js"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r012",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "architecture",
      "content": "Claude Code has 5 permission modes: default (prompt each tool), acceptEdits (auto-accept file edits), plan (read-only), dontAsk (deny unless pre-approved), bypassPermissions (skip all checks). The dashboard should be aware of the current mode and adjust its behavior — e.g., in acceptEdits mode, only non-edit tools trigger approval requests.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "documentation",
        "artifact": "Claude Code permissions reference",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "permissions",
        "modes"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r013",
      "type": "risk",
      "topic": "architecture",
      "content": "The PermissionRequest hook timeout (default 30s) is the window for a human to approve/deny remotely. If the user doesn't respond in time, the hook times out and falls through to local terminal prompt. For mobile/slow connections, may need to extend timeout to 120-300s, but this stalls Claude Code's entire session.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "analysis",
        "artifact": null,
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "documented",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
      "timestamp": "2026-03-11T01:00:00Z",
      "conflicts_with": [],
      "resolved_by": null,
      "tags": [
        "timeout",
        "UX",
        "latency"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "r014",
      "type": "factual",
      "topic": "prior-art",
      "content": "Several community projects wrap Claude Code as a subprocess for remote access (claude-code-server, claude-code-webui, CloudeCode, 247-claude-code-remote). None intercept the permission system remotely via hooks — they either pre-approve tools or relay stdin/stdout. Our HTTP hook approach would be novel.",
      "source": {
        "origin": "web",
        "artifact": "GitHub community projects",
        "connector": null
      },
      "evidence": "web",
      "status": "active",
      "phase_added": "research",
